M2Amiga is a programming system for the language Modula-2 for the Amiga.
It includes a compiler which supports the full line of 680xx processors
and has an integrated assembler, a linker which allows linking with
object files produced by other compilers/assembler if they are using
the Amiga link file format, a post-mortem source-level debugger which
allows very easy inspection of even complex datastructures and a simple
editor. An extension package is available, which inludes a special
linker allowing to make devices and libraries, a profiler and the
sources to some the modules included with M2Amiga.

The compiler of version 4.1 was extended to support constants of record-
and array types. And the interface modules of 4.1 were extended to support
the new WB2.1.

M2Amiga runs on all Amigas with WB1.3 or newer. It is suggested, that
you have a harddisk and at least 1MB of RAM. The demo version is not so
demanding, so you could use it on smaller systems.

